# Ignore everything ...
*
**/*

# ... except subdirectories containing a .gitignore ...
# NOTE: This causes a scan of all subdirectories, looking for .gitignore files.
#   To prevent scans of huge/slow directories add a .gitignore to explicitly
#   ignore all subdirectories, as in:
#     ./Library/CloudStorage/.gitignore
!**/
!**/.gitignore
tmp/**/
trash/**/

# these have to be explicitly ignored because they sometimes contain git repos
.cargo/
.cache/
.opam/
.git/
.local/share/pnpm
.goenv/
.zkbd/

# dontcare:
.fzf/

# binaries and local files
.vscode
.aider*
.env

# redo-based test/check harness: narrow opt-in landed ahead of this file's
# full ignore-scheme reconciliation (deny-first here vs. svelte-crostini's
# allowlist-of-ignores), which is still a separate, later effort.
!test.do
!default.tested.do
!default.checked.do
!HACKING.md

# shell config unification (.profile/.bashrc/.config/sh/** convergence):
# same narrow-opt-in precedent as the harness block above -- .config/sh/**
# itself is already trackable via .config/.gitignore's un-ignore-non-dotfiles
# rule.
!.profile_test.sh
!.bashrc_test.sh
